This is a 5 minute review.  Saying the app is gorgeous would be an overstatement.  It's very cute and slightly awkward, however for the intended audience it's very good.  This app is an amusement and great to help pass the time for kids as well as adults.  I love the tranquil nature of the app.  As many have pointed out, the world is far too small.  The largest gripe   by far is the lack of saving progress.  It's takes but a few minutes to create a beautiful world, but there's no saving.  Even for a kid, this is a HUGE disappointment.  For that reason alone I can not recommend buying this app even as an amusement for kids.  The graphics are nothing to shout praise over, however I prefer the simple style of graphics.  The interaction is fun.  But due to the lack of what I would consider key features, the apps feels more like a half finished experiment than an app you would actually purchase.  Feels more like playing a demo than a completed app.  The 3 star rating is for potential.  Absolutely fantastic concept.  Please expand the world and offer a save option.  Connecting with Google Play would be nice too.
